Two fishermen are feared dead after their boat capsized in Lake Naivasha on Wednesday night.One was rescued by other fishermen hours after the accident in Kasarani area, 50kms from Naivasha town.&ldquo;The winds were very strong and we could not navigate fast due to the water hyacinth and this led to the accident. I am glad that I was saved,&rdquo; said James Sankale.The incident comes barely a week after two fishermen drowned near Karagita landing beach while casting their nets. The latest victims are from Karagita estate, Naivasha. The death of the two brings to eight the number of fishermen who have died in the lake this year.Leader Joseph Mwaura, known as Kamjesh, said fishermen need life-jackets to keep them from drowning.